\section{Conclusion}

A rational approximation of the Dawson\text{'s} integral is derived and implemented for rapid and highly accurate computation of the complex error function. The computational test we performed shows the accuracy exceeding $\sim {10^{ - 14}}$ in the domain of practical importance $0 \le y < 0.1 \cap \left| {x + iy} \right| \le 8$. A Matlab code for computation of the complex error function covering the entire complex plane is presented.

